text: Stangeia siceliota is a moth of the family Pterophoridae that is known from Yemen, China and southern Europe. It is also known from Turkey and Armenia. ==References== Category:Oxyptilini Category:Moths described in 1847 Category:Moths of Asia Category:Moths of the Arabian Peninsula Category:Moths of Europe Category:Moths of Turkey Category:Taxa named by Philipp Christoph Zeller
